      "title": "Ask HN: Has anyone replaced Claude/GPT with a local model for daily coding?",
      "url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48542100",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48542100",
      "score": 1041,
      "comments": 456,
      "author": "cloudking",
      "published": "2026-06-15T14:46:53Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Developers are replacing Claude/GPT with Qwen-2.5-Coder (14B/32B) and DeepSeek-Coder-V2 for daily local development workflows.",
        "Tooling relies heavily on Ollama or llama.cpp backends paired with the Continue.dev VS Code/JetBrains extension for inline autocompletion.",
        "Viable performance (30+ tok/s) requires Apple Silicon (M3 Max/Ultra) or 24GB VRAM GPUs like the RTX 4090 running GGUF quants."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
