      "category": "security",
      "title": "Curl will not accept vulnerability reports during July 2026",
      "url": "https://daniel.haxx.se/blog/2026/06/15/curl-summer-of-bliss/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48537165",
      "score": 769,
      "comments": 307,
      "author": "secret-noun",
      "published": "2026-06-15T06:02:57Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Lead maintainer Daniel Stenberg's planned sabbatical in July 2026 means zero upstream vulnerability triaging or CVE assignments during this period.",
        "Security researchers must delay submissions, as curl's HackerOne and email reporting channels will pause triage for the entire month.",
        "DevSecOps teams should expect a freeze on official curl patches and anticipate a potential influx of disclosures in August 2026."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
